"""
Write a Python program that ask user to input two numbers. Check if both numbers are divisible by 2 or
3, if yes multiply them and print them on screen. If not, add them and then print it on screen. 
"""

num1 = int(input("enter a number: "))
num2 = int(input("enter a number: "))
if ((num1 % 2 == 0) or (num1 % 3 == 0)) and ((num2 % 2 == 0) or (num2 % 3 == 0)):
    result = num1 * num2
    print(result)
else:
    result = num1 + num2
    print(result)
